Do you want to play this fun word game with me? After you watch the video, come up with your own word and put it in the comments! It’s addicting!

This word building activity will engage all your students while teaching prefixes, suffixes, spelling patterns, and new vocabulary! You can use this as a center or partner work, enrichment homework, whole or small group instruction, or even a five minute filler! If the link in my profile doesn’t work because it’s a video, message me for the link to this resource.  bit.ly/expandaword

This is how I group my students for remediation and it’s great for test prep groups/remediation. These formatives are a quick easy way to assess my math students. I created these rigorous mini-math assessments (five questions, one page) for each math standard in fourth grade. A (Form B) was also created to give my students another opportunity to show growth and learning. These tools drive my instruction and small group learning all year! 
Digital version with Google Slides and answer keys included.
5th grade is also available. 😊
Direct message me for the link to my TPT store, specify if you want 4th or 5th grade. #math #mathteacher #mathassessments

Our FIRST Tune Tuesday is in the books and I think this class is going to love close reading! 

Each week I know I will see improvement as I teach and introduce new skills. I just love how excited they were about this! 🙌

*Swipe to see it in action! 

Close reading with music engages all my learners! They look forward to reading the text multiple times and finding evidence to prove their thinking!

During Tune Tuesday (can be done any day of the week! 😝) we will: 

•close read
•annotate the text
•determine the theme 
•appreciate author’s craft 
•learn new vocabulary
•find figurative language
•author’s point of view 
•tone/mood
•cite evidence 
•use accountable talk 
•debate with our classmates
•and of course, sing along! 

If you want to try something new this year, you have to try Tune Tuesday with your class!

There’s a digital version using Google Slides to all the sets!

Link in profile to volume 1 bundle, (this song is featured in volume 1, set one).

node.text:
Student Lottery: Fun way for students to WIN random selection! Student Lottery can be used for mystery student selection, tasks or jobs, partner selection, desk checks, extra incentives, the possibilities are endless! I placed it on my desk this morning and my students waited with anticipation! The sound of the ping pong balls moving around adds instant excitement to student picking!

One tip: If you’re using the student lottery for academic questioning, pull the ball first, so you can differentiate your questions for each student after you pull it and know what type/level of difficulty they need.

All student names are on the ping pong balls, plus a few extra special ones. Ping pong balls from Dollar Tree and plastic fish bowl from Petco. I saw this brilliant idea from @fantasticallyfourth a few years ago and wanted to add it to our classroom again! #bts #bts21 #backtoschool #classroomideas

node.text:
Here are my students’ First Week Favorites. ❤️

Take some time and reflect at the end of each week/month to see what excited or engaged your students. This gives them a voice and makes them feel their opinions matter and are valued. It also gives you appreciation for all the hard work you put into their favorites! 🙌 (Took less than five minutes at the end of the day Friday.) We forgot a few things because we were in a hurry, but I’m glad they think they had a great week! ❤️

This is a great gauge for me to see what they liked or interested them. It helps me to plan future lessons, activities, or management tools in our classroom. I’m excited to see there was a nice balance of learning/fun favorites!

#firstweekofschool #backtoschool #teacherlife
